programme.desc: A look at bizarre dinosaurs such as the curious buck-toothed Exipdexipteryx, the amazing four-winged Microraptor and the pot-bellied Nothronychus.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: In 2000, scientists made a groundbreaking discovery, explaining how birds evolved from dinosaurs. However, a deeper investigation put a question mark over everything.
programme.sub-title: The Dinosaur That Fooled the World

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Exploring a dinosaur graveyard in Patagonia to gain a better understanding of dinosaur evolution, particularly the Middle Jurassic period when they became gigantic.

programme.title: Living with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: David Attenborough learns that descendants of the dinosaur age are alive and well. David explores how they survived the catastrophes that wiped out other species.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Until recently most scientists thought they knew what killed off the dinosaurs. It was a 10 km-wide meteorite which smashed into Yucatan in Mexico.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Exploring the newfound remains of a dinosaur species considered the biggest carnivore in history, all while posing the question whether they engaged in a fight against the Argentinasaurus.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds
programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado
programme.desc: Venezuela is famous for its lost worlds, its forbidding mountains, huge swamps, and impenetrable jungles, all seemingly cut off in space and time. Yet each is linked, by the mighty river: the Orinoco, the rumoured route to El Dorado, city of gold.
programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds
programme.desc: The Amazon is the largest rainforest in the world, and the richest ecosystem on earth. This film uncovers what makes the Amazon such a powerhouse of evolution; how it has come to home a third of all species on the planet.

programme.title: Santa's Dog
programme.desc: Hercules is a special dog which Santa has named the 'Naughty and Nice List Maker.' Hercules' duty is to select one child each year on the Naughty List and give that child the opportunity to make it to the Nice List.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Wildfires
programme.desc: With flames roaring to heights of 50 meters or more and temperatures exceeding 1,200°C, the wildfire is one of Mother Nature’s most horrific killers. Wildfires show no signs of stopping and their inexorability on this planet is truly terrifying.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MANMADE
programme.desc: When it comes to disasters, mother nature has mankind beat. However, as mankind expands, evolves and technology advances, it comes with dangerous challenges. When errors are made or unforeseen circumstances occur, the results can be devastating.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: TORNADO
programme.desc: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air extending from the base of a thunderstorm down to the ground. Tornadoes are capable of completely destroying well-made structures, uprooting trees, and hurling objects through the air like deadly missiles.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MEGAFLOODS
programme.desc: Water covers two thirds of the earth’s surface, and we are utterly dependent on it, but when this vital ingredient of life unleashes its fury on the planet it becomes the ultimate bringer of death.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: EARTHQUAKES
programme.desc: Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates suddenly slip causing shock waves to shake the surface of the Earth. They occur on fault lines - the most active are the Ring of Fire in the Pacific Ocean and the San Andreas fault on America’s west coast.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: CONSTRUCTION
programme.desc: Bridges and tunnels have transformed the way we live, making the inaccessible easy to reach, and turning time consuming journeys into convenient commutes, but when things go wrong they can go very wrong indeed.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: AIR, LAND AND SEA
programme.desc: Planes, trains and ships, our mass transit systems, have had a profound effect on mankind, making the world smaller and more connected.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: HURRICANES
programme.desc: Hurricanes, Typhoons and Cyclones all the same thing with different names – what they also have in common is their destructive power! Hurricanes are large, swirling storms and winds from a hurricane can damage buildings or trees.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: VOLCANOES
programme.desc: Volcanoes are Earth’s geologic architects. They’ve created more than 80 percent of our planet’s surface and their explosive force has crafted both mountains and craters.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Wild Weather Season
programme.desc: 2005 seemed to be the year that Earth went wild. Follow George as he brings us back to the site of his hairiest adventures from that year.

programme.title: Angry Planet: West Coast Winter Weather
programme.desc: On Canada's rugged West Coast, George ice-climbs a frozen waterfall, uses ski-skins to climb Mt.Garibaldi to an alpine lake, visits a storm-watching lodge on British Columbia's Long Beach, home of winter surfing and massive Pacific storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Waterspouts
programme.desc: In the Florida Keys, George uses a motorboat, a van and small plane to get up close to waterspouts - the nautical cousins of tornadoes. He also meets some of the 25 million alligators that live in the Sunshine State.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Island Caving
programme.desc: Accompanied by a group of hardcore cavers from Alberta and British Columbia, George descends into spectacular caves that lead deep into the earth on Vancouver Island. The team carries inflatable kayaks to explore a dark underground river.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Desert Monsoon
programme.desc: Enlisting the help of fellow storm chaser R.J. Evans, George heads to Arizona to photograph spectacular lightning storms triggered by the desert monsoon season. R.J. however is known as "America's noisiest athiest" for his free-thought radio show.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Polynesian Volcanoes
programme.desc: In New Zealand, George learns that an undersea volcano 1000 miles North in Tonga is creating a new island. After nautical mishaps, clad in nothing but underwear and a life jacket, George becomes one of the first explorers on this new land.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Java: Land of Fire
programme.desc: In the Pacific Ring of Fire island of Java, George explores new ash eruptions from Anak Krakatau, whose 1883 eruption shook the world. He travels to Merapi and descends into Kawah Ijen to explore the world's largest lake of sulfuric acid.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Highway to Hail
programme.desc: George and his team head into "bears' cage", looking to get beat up by the biggest, baddest hailstones in Texas and Oklahoma. Their storm chasing vehicles don't look too pretty after coming through these massive storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Costa Rica
programme.desc: George explores the volcanoes of Costa Rica with an international team of scientists, rafts down white water rivers in full flood, rappels down raging waterfalls, and handles some of deadliest snakes this tropical country has to offer.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Winds Of Autumn
programme.desc: This year he starts off by getting prepared in a wind tunnel, then he and his chase partner Mark Robinson head to Newfoundland for more wild weather action. Then, it's off to another encounter where the wild wind fans a raging inferno.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Iceland: Fire and Ice
programme.desc: George meets President of Iceland Ólafur Grímsson who spearheaded use of geothermal power; visits Blue Lagoon and geysers; explores volcanically active Haimaey Island and climbs an iceberg calving off the glaciers at Vatnajokull Lagoon.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hurricane Triple Threat

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The second world war was conflict on an unprecedented scale. Its battles set new marks for the sheer size of forces deployed and for the power of their weapons. In this episode we study the first battle at sea, and the largest army to have ever marched.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A war that reached every continent and touched every sort of terrain demanded every sort of strategy. In this episode we examine battles fought at sea, and in the jungle, in city streets, invasions from the air, and retreats from the land.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Battles are almost always about territory. Advancing the front line, seizing the port, the city, the oil field. The fate of nations in the war rose and fell on battles that took territory. Singapore, Monte Casino, Stalingrad...all about territory.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Every war seized new tactics; some inspired, some desperate, all attempting to influence the course of battles. Campaigns waged against non military targets to demoralize. Suicide missions launched when traditional weapons failed. Rules were rewritten.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A world war is a patchwork of actions. Land. Sea. Air. Massive, or small scale. The stories of these actions, are just as varied. This episode describes battles of amphibious forces, climate, geography, and the problems of supply.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Through history, armies marched to face each other on favored ground and clashed to decide a campaign, a war, an empire. With the 20th century that changed. The battles of the WWII happened anywhere and everywhere, in every weather and climate.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Some words transcend their origins as humble place names. They are carved into history as turning points which influenced the course of WWII, the fate of nations, and the make-up of our world. El Alameine, Okinawa, and Pearl Harbor.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Aristocrat and the Balkan Communists
programme.desc: Fitzroy Maclean, an MP and WWII spy, supported Tito's Communist partisans in Yugoslavia against the Germans, forging a lasting friendship and honored at Tito's funeral post-war.
programme.sub-title: The Aristocrat and the Balkan Communists

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Agent Garbo
programme.desc: Juan Pujol, MI6's WWII agent "Garbo," created a fictitious spy network in Lisbon, deceiving the Germans with crucial disinformation and influencing their strategies. After the war, MI6 protected him, and he lived in Venezuela until his death in 1988.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Christine Granville
programme.desc: Christine Granville, aka Krystyna Skarbek, a brave SOE agent, secured the release of captured comrades from the Gestapo before Operation Dragoon, earning the George Medal.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The French Triple Agent
programme.desc: Operation Cockade, led by MI6's double agent Henri Dericourt in 1943, aimed to deceive Germans with sabotage. Despite efforts, Germans withdrew divisions unconvinced. Dericourt faced a post-war treason trial and died in a mysterious 1962 plane crash.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Spymistress and the French Fiasco
programme.desc: After WWII, SOE disbanded, leaving Vera Atkins to uncover fates of 118 agents, including 13 women. Many were betrayed and sent to camps; some were executed. Atkins' quest continued, marked by personal impact and delayed recognition.
programme.sub-title: The Spymistress and the French Fiasco

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The SAS Italian Job
programme.desc: In 1945, during the Italian Spring offensive, SOE agent Michael Lees and SAS officer Roy Farran led a raid on German HQs at Villa Rossi and Villa Calvi. Despite orders to cancel, Farran attacked with SAS men and partisans, killing many Germans.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Dutch Disaster
programme.desc: Operation North Pole was a WWII German deception using captured SOE agents to mislead Britain. 47 of 50 agents were captured. Despite warnings, SOE ignored signs of compromise to maintain support, leading to a major intelligence failure.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Scholar and the Fight for Greece
programme.desc: Monty Woodhouse, a professor and a legend for blowing up the Gorgopotamos Bridge in Greece in 1942. In the British counter attack against Rommell at Al Alamein in North Africa it was vital to disrupt German supply routes, Greece.
programme.sub-title: The Scholar and the Fight for Greece

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Banker, the Norwegians & the Bomb
programme.desc: Sir Charles attended Eton, and then joined the Coldstream Guards. He won the Military Cross on the Western Front and, having survived the war, returned to banking.
programme.sub-title: The Banker, the Norwegians & the Bomb

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Double Agent Tricycle
programme.desc: Dusan Popov was almost certainly James Bond. Ian Fleming knew all the stories about him. Popov managed to persuade both the Germans and MI6 to keep him in the style of a millionaire businessman while performing a series of missions against the Nazis.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Mafia Connection
programme.desc: Lucky Luciano, a mafia boss of the 1930s, was in jail in 1942 on charges of running prostitution rings. US intelligence services did a deal with him and he got the Italians to share intelligence on German U boat movements.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: War Without Boundaries
programme.desc: War Without Boundaries: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The Means To Victory

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The World At War
programme.desc: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Terror of The World

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Armageddon 1943-1945
programme.desc: Armageddon 1943-1945: The defeat at Stalingrad in 1943 was the turning point of the war and convinced the Nazi leadership to intensify their terror and propaganda campaigns.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Power Generator
programme.desc: A three hundred and ninety ton giant on a daring journey: A team of German heavy-lift-specialists have to transport a generator from a disused coal plant to its new operation site 120 kilometers away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: ITER Magnet
programme.desc: This giant magnet will revolutionize the world and energy production in the future. The world's largest nuclear fusion reactor is currently under construction in southern France.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Drilling Rig
programme.desc: A brand-new oil rig, worth 500 million dollar, has to go from South Korea to Europe. The problem is that it is too gigantic for a heavy transport vessel. The solution is to tow it.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Siberian Ice Road
programme.desc: A Mega Transport on one of the most dangerous roads in the world. The Siberian Ice Road. It doesn't forgive mistakes. It's treacherous. And unpredictable.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Giant Antenna
programme.desc: South America. The chelonian Atacama Desert is home to the world's largest radio telescope Atacama Large Millimeter Array Observatory, also known as ALMA.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Mining Truck
programme.desc: If a transporter needs to be transported, if 176 wheels aren't enough to carry its weight and if the load weighs twice as much as the transporter... Then it must be the mother of all mega transports!

programme.title: Mega Transports: Wind Park
programme.desc: A wind park needs to get from Europe to Asia. Over two thousand tons of highly sensitive and valuable cargo. On one of the world's largest heavy lift vessels.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Gigantic Autoliner
programme.desc: A transport to the other side of the globe. The Höegh Trapper is the largest automobile transporter in the world. Two hundred meters long, thirty-six meters wide.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Biggest Containership
programme.desc: When the first ship of the brand-new OOCL-fleet gets underway, more cargo is moved at one time than anywhere else in the world and ever before.

programme.title: Mega Transports: AutoClav
programme.desc: A unique mega transport made of steel and titanium with a special purpose: to extract tons of gold. This so-called autoclave is the biggest of its kind. Its weight: over one thousand tons.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Superyachts
programme.desc: Transporting a ship by a ship - this becomes necessary when the super-rich want their super yacht available on the other side of the world, but do not want to sail it there themselves.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Villagemove
programme.desc: Everyone knows it: Housemoving is a lot of work, requires excellent planning and costs time and money. Just imagine how it must be if you are moving an entire village - as a whole.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Conveyance of the Norwegian Joy
programme.desc: Meyer Werft in Germany is one of the biggest shipbuilders in the world. But it's problem is as big as the ships it builds: the coast and sea are 50 kilometres away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Antonov
programme.desc: A giant of the skies - the Antonov AN-124-100M-150. Worldwide the biggest production cargo aircraft of all time. No aircraft can transport more goods than the Russian giant.

programme.title: Top 10: Architecture: THEATRES AND OPERA HOUSES & UNFORGETTABLE EXPERIENCES

programme.title: Top 10: Architecture: MUSEUMS AND GALLERIES & ARCHITECTURAL TREASURES
programme.desc: Bilbao, Amsterdam, Antwerp and Florence belong to a dynamic group of cities that preserve the heritage of humanity through museums.

programme.title: Alien Contact: UFO Invaders
programme.desc: Hundreds of UFOs have crashed on Earth. Mankind has witnessed these crashes, communicated with the visitors, even left our planet with them once they are able to return to their worlds, but the most shocking revelation is the reason why they come.

programme.title: Confessions Of An Alien Abductee
programme.desc: Chantelle, Marie and Simon are all alien abductees. These ordinary people share their extraordinary stories as they seek help through the curiously named Anomalous Mind Management Abductee Contactee Helpline, or AMMACH.

programme.title: Alien Cyclops: The Extraordinary Case of Sagrada Familia
programme.desc: In 1963 Brazil, three children witness a UFO in their backyard. An alien cyclops descends, and Mr. Alberto investigates the phenomenon.

programme.title: From the Mothman to the Reptilians: A Guide to Alien Species
programme.desc: Witnesses from around the world have had close encounters with extraterrestrial races, shaping our imagination and becoming cultural phenomena.

programme.title: UFO Hunters II: Tales from the Universe
programme.desc: Italian ufologists explore alien evidence in history & folklore. Have we been watched since ancient times?

programme.title: 27 Alien Encounters
programme.desc: Strange and bizarre UFO encounters abound, but recent Alien encounters by highly credible eyewitnesses are so unusual and perplexing that they challenge our understanding of physics and the Universe as we know it.

programme.title: Area 51, Roswell Crash, Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Area 51 is located at the center of UFO research and legends of extra-terrestrial folklore. It is located six hundred miles west of Roswell, New Mexico, where the infamous Roswell UFO crashed in 1947. Also in this episode The Allagash Alien Abductions .

programme.title: Ancient Aliens and the New World Order 2
programme.desc: Recent discoveries reveal that a highly advanced race of extraterrestrial beings came to Earth in our ancient past, but the shocking realization is that they are still here now, among us and may have a sinister agenda beyond our wildest imaginations.

programme.title: Abducted by Aliens: UFO Encounters of the 4th Kind
programme.desc: Are we being taken by beings from outer space or another dimension? A troubling phenomenon has been occurring for centuries.

programme.title: Ancient Engineers: Aliens On Earth
programme.desc: Our evolution may be influenced by our ancestors and their Gods. We are not alone in the universe.

programme.title: Ancient Alien America
programme.desc: Native cultures have handed down shocking accounts for generations of Aliens from other worlds visiting Earth in the ancient past and their involvement with them.

programme.title: Aliens in Egypt
programme.desc: New evidence of highly advanced, precision machining on Egypt's Giza Plateau gives credence to the Ancient Alien hypothesis further supported by glyphs of futuristic vehicles, bizarre flywheels, and other artifacts and monuments cut with laser precision.

programme.title: Dulce Base: The New Illuminati
programme.desc: Dulce, New Mexico is a hotspot for mysterious phenomena and alleged secret military collaboration between humans and aliens.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: Texas UFO
programme.desc: This episode includes: Scared to Death, Texas UFO, Butch Cassidy and Sibling Search & Update.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Ellie is told by a fortune teller that she must resolve her past and make amends with all of those she ghosted before Christmas and discovers love in the process.

programme.title: Finding Father Christmas
programme.desc: Christmas for Miranda is a painful reminder of the family she never had. Her mother died when she was young, never revealing the identity of her father. But, three days before Christmas, she unexpectedly receives a clue.

programme.title: Our Italian Christmas Memories
programme.desc: The Colucci siblings, in an effort to jog the memory of their grandfather who is struggling with dementia, set out to recreate their late grandmother’s legendary pasta sauce.

programme.title: Candy Cane Christmas
programme.desc: As Phoebe is searching for a new tradition to lift her holiday spirits, she realizes that it's not the traditions we cherish, but the people with whom we share them.

programme.title: All Saints Christmas
programme.desc: Lisette is a popular R&B singer who’s getting ready to travel home to New Orleans for Christmas.

programme.title: The Holiday Sitter
programme.desc: When Sam, a workaholic bachelor, babysits his niece and nephew before the holidays, he recruits help from their handsome neighbor Jason and finds himself in an unexpected romance.

programme.title: A Family Christmas Gift
programme.desc: When Amber spends the holidays with her Aunt Dora and helps plan a fundraising Christmas Concert, it brings Amber closer to her aunt and a new love into her life.

programme.title: Battle of the Bulbs
programme.desc: Dueling neighbours whose Christmas decorating rivalry turns so outrageous, it puts the 'No' in 'Noel' for the small town sponsoring the annual Fete.

programme.title: December Bride
programme.desc: The last person Layla O’Reilly wants as her date to the wedding between her ex-fiancé and her own cousin is Seth Murphy, the one who introduced the soon-to-be-married couple. But it’s better than showing up alone.

programme.title: Magic Stocking
programme.desc: A young widow finds a tattered old Christmas stocking at a Holiday craft sale, but is skeptical of its magic when it seems to create small trinkets on its own.

programme.title: In Merry Measure
programme.desc: When pop star Darcy returns home to spend Christmas with her sister and niece, she unexpectedly finds herself coaching the high school choir with her onetime rival, Adam.

programme.title: Lay Down Your Heart
programme.desc: An accomplished artist, a lifelong performer and a person with Down syndrome, Niall McNeil has built a unique family tree of blood and chosen relations made up of his closest friends and collaborators.

programme.title: Worth Every Minute
programme.desc: A tribute to Pat Schulz, a working-class heroine known for her '50s human and workers' rights battles. This documentary offers a historical view of the women's movement, tracing its roots, early issues, current concerns, and emerging directions.

programme.title: I Want To Be An Engineer
programme.desc: This film provides a lively introduction to the professional and personal lives of three female engineers--just a few of the growing number of women who are opting for "non-traditional" jobs.

programme.title: Waterwalker
programme.desc: Accompany Bill Mason on a canoe journey through Ontario's wilderness, from Lake Superior to the river's source. Enjoy breathtaking visuals, whitewater excitement, and Mason's reflections on nature, art, and canoeing, with Bruce Cockburn's music.

programme.title: The Man Who Stole Dreams
programme.desc: This enchanting and magical animation film, an ode to our dreams during the night, celebrates the creative imagination, uniqueness, and the human spirit. The plot involves a man who steals the dreams of villagers, the tries to sell them back to the them.

programme.title: Yul 871
programme.desc: A Paris engineer on Flight YUL 871 to Montréal seeks his displaced parents amid the restlessness of the era. Amidst a brief love affair and Expo visits, he finds connection with a little girl.

programme.title: A Love Affair With Politics A Portrait Of Marion Dewar
programme.desc: This spirited documentary on one of Canada's most successful female politicians was filmed while she was mayor of Ottawa. Dewar talks of her political career as a natural extension of her roles of wife, mother, public-health nurse and ordinary citizen.

programme.title: Return Home
programme.desc: Return Home touchingly explores intergenerational relations while capturing the spirit and experiences of early Chinese-Canadian immigrants and their role in Canadian history.

programme.title: Junior
programme.desc: Reflecting our society, the world of junior hockey is obsessed with competition. Taking in one complete season with the Baie-Comeau Drakkar, this film reveals the daily lives of managers and players on this Quebec Major Junior Hockey League team.

programme.title: Star Wars Kid The Rise Of The Digital Shadows
programme.desc: Ghyslain Raza, better known as the “Star Wars Kid,” breaks his silence to reflect on our hunger for content and the right to be forgotten in the digital age.

programme.title: The Way It Is
programme.desc: The Way It Is" explores divorce's effects on a family, centered on twelve-year-old Helen. Her journey to acceptance offers insights for all ages, suitable for family-life courses, single-parent groups, and counseling.

programme.title: Perfecting The Art Of Longing
programme.desc: Using footage from security cameras, video calls and home-video archives, this experimental short film leads us on a journey through memory, family and faith, exploring the nature of connection and distance.

programme.title: Christophers Movie Matinee
programme.desc: When movie cameras were put in the hands of a few young people, they made this film about themselves and their world. The film is revealing in what it shows of a dissenting generation and its rationale.

programme.title: Mary Two-Axe Earley I Am Indian Again
programme.desc: This film shares the powerful story of Mary Two-Axe Earley, who fought for more than two decades to challenge sex discrimination against First Nations women embedded in Canada’s Indian Act and became a key figure in Canada’s women’s rights movement.

programme.title: Notmans World
programme.desc: William Notman was a man of rare talent. Photography was still in its infancy when he opened his first studio--in Montréal--in the late 1850s. He rapidly turned his art, and a budding technology, into a highly successful business.

programme.title: Nails
programme.desc: A blacksmith is seen labouring at his forge, shaping nails from single strands of steel rods. It then shifts from this setting to the roar of a twentieth-century nail mill, where machines, cut, and pound the steel rods faster than the eye can follow.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Service In The Sky
programme.desc: Made in 1957, this film glamorizes a service job in which minor emergencies appear as serious and absorbing challenges. Marriage is assumed to be the natural end of the middle-class woman's working life.

programme.title: Long Time Comin
programme.desc: There is a cultural revolution going on in Canada and Faith Nolan and Grace Channer are on the leading edge. These two African-Canadian lesbian artists give back to art its most urgent meanings--commitment and passion.

programme.title: The Tender Tale Of Cinderella Penguin
programme.desc: Medieval-style animation twists Cinderella with a mistreated penguin. Hilarity ensues when she loses her magic flipper, saved by Prince Charming. A wordless film with a unique fairy tale twist.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Wings On Her Shoulder
programme.desc: This is a 1943 recruitment film. Although it specifically promises women jobs in post-war aviation, its primary message is that women fulfill support positions "so that men might fly.

programme.title: Proudest Girl In The World, The
programme.desc: A musical recruiting film for the Canadian Women's Army Corp.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Die 12 Weihnachtsgeschenke
programme.desc: Als Anna, eine arbeitslose Malerin, nicht mehr über die Runden kommt, wird sie als persönliche Weihnachtseinkäuferin für Marc, einen verklemmten Firmenchef, eingestellt.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Ich bin nicht bereit für Weihnachten
programme.desc: Hollys energiegeladenes, karriereorientiertes Leben gerat vollig aus den Fugem, als sie feststellt, dass sie nicht mehr lugen kann, weil der Weihnachtsmann ihrer Nichte Anna einen besonderen Wunsch erfullt hat.

programme.title: Weihnachten auf königliche Art
programme.desc: Kristin Cooper, die hübsche und talentierte Assistentin einer globalen PR-Firma, wird mit der Leitung der jährlichen Weihnachtsmodenschau und -auktion für den Bekleidungsunternehmer Mr. Carson beauftragt.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Weihnachten in Glenbrooke – Verliebt in die Millionärin
programme.desc: Jessica, Millionen-Erbin und bald CEO eines mächtigen Unternehmens, ist trotz ihres privilegierten Lebens unglücklich. Inkognito reist sie in den kleinen Geburtsort ihrer Mutter, um dort Weihnachten zu verbringen...

programme.title: Weihnachtswunderland
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtszeit in New York ist für die erfolglose Künstlerin Heidi Neill alles andere als wundervoll.

programme.title: Mistelzweige küsst man nicht
programme.desc: Zu Weihnachten kehrt Darcy nach Hause zurück und läuft dort ihrem Highschool-Erzfeind Luke über den Weg. Als beide bei der Vorbereitung einer weihnachtlichen Wohltätigkeitsgala helfen, erkennen sie, dass ihre bisherige Abneigung womöglich voreilig war.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Weihnachtsmann gesucht
programme.desc: Weihnachten, das Fest der Liebe, steht vor der Tür. Für Johannes (Christoph Waltz), einen etwas verschrobenen Zoohändler, droht dieses jedoch zum schlimmsten seines Lebens zu werden.

programme.title: Unsere Lehrerin die Weihnachtshexe
programme.desc: Während des Tages ist Paola eine gewöhnliche Grundschullehrerin, doch nachts verwandelt sie sich in die Weihnachtshexe, eine magische Wesenheit, die den braven Kindern Geschenke macht.

programme.title: Hallo, ich bin der Weihnachtsmann!
programme.desc: Nachdem der Weihnachtsmann aus seinem Schlitten fällt und eine Amnesie erleidet, kann ihn nur die Unschuld eines kleinen Kindes retten.

programme.title: Weihnachten mit Hindernissen
programme.desc: Vicky und Jason haben sich schon längst getrennt. Aber ihre beiden Kinder bringen sie dazu, die Weihnachtsferien gemeinsam zu verbringen. Als dann auch noch Vickys Boss und Jasons Assistentin auftauchen, wird es immer turbulenter...

programme.title: Casamento De Natal
programme.desc: Maggie é uma editora literária cujo hobby é criar oportunidades de relacionamento entre seus amigos. Quando seu ex-namorado aparece como um autor recém-contratado e bem-sucedido, Maggie precisa examinar suas decisões anteriores.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor
programme.desc: Na noite de Natal, o xerife Rick parece ter perdido seu espírito natalino. Quando prende um homem acusado de invadir as casas da vizinhança, o xerife não sabe o que fazer quando o invasor declara ser o Papai Noel em pessoa.

programme.title: José e Maria
programme.desc: Em 30a.C., Herodes reinava sob Israel até que o nascimento do Messias ameaçava a sua soberania. Surge então nessa jornada de fé e milagres uma mulher, Maria e um homem, José, escolhidos por de Deus para cuidar daquele que salvaria a humanidade, Jesus.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: Um Amor Inesperado
programme.desc: É Natal e Sammi está buscando um pouco de sossego. Viciado em trabalho, Seth vem da cidade grande para explorar um terreno que recebeu de herança e que ele pretende vender antes do final do ano. A tranquilidade de Sammi é interrompida pela chegada de Seth

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Antes Só Do Que Mal Acompanhado
programme.desc: Neal só que voltar para Chicago e passar o Dia de Ação de Graças com sua família. Mas ele só se dá mal. Tudo culpa de Del Griffith — um vendedor desbocado que leva Neal a uma busca sem sentido.

programme.title: Aventuras do K-9: Uma História de Natal
programme.desc: Kassie, suas amigas e seu cachorro, Scoot, organizam um evento de arrecadação de fundos de férias, mas precisam proteger o dinheiro de alguns bandidos para salvar o Natal.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.sub-title: Wham! / Justin Bieber / Katy Perry / The Killers / Ariana Grande / Andrea Bocelli / Alessia Cara

programme.title: MTV Xmas
programme.desc: Bing Crosby (White Christmas) / Mariah Carey (Joy To The World) / Lady Antebellum (A Holly Jolly Christmas) / Chris Rea (Driving Home For Christmas) / Spice Girls (2 Become 1) / Peter Auty (Walking In The Air)
programme.sub-title: Bing Crosby / Mariah Carey / Lady Antebellum / Chris Rea / Spice Girls / Peter Auty

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Andreas lange Reise führt ihn schließlich und endlich in den Busch – ins „echte“ Afrika. Hier begibt er sich auf die Fährte der typischsten wilden Afrikaner – der Big Five. Und wo könnte er das besser als im Krüger Nationalpark, dem Wahrzeichen Südafrikas.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Inmitten von himmlisch schönen Bergeshöhen thront der Piz Beverin über dem Naturpark, dem er seinen Namen verleiht. Zu seinen Füßen erstreckt sich eine Landschaft voller wilder Natur. Tiefe Schluchten und glasklare Bergseen, artenreiche Trockenwiesen und seltene Moore, majestätische Steinböcke und zurückkehrende Wölfe.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Venezuela
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Wildes Portugal: Vom Flachland bis in die Berge
programme.desc: Portugal ist ein kleines Land, jedoch bekannt für abwechslungsreiche Landschaften. Korkeichenwälder im Süden am Targus-Fluss und bewaldete Berge am Douro-Fluss im Norden. Entsprechend vielfältig ist die Tierwelt, die wir kennenlernen.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Türkei
programme.desc: Im Mittleren Osten trifft Ost auf West, Wälder treffen auf Wüsten, die Tierwelt ist erstaunlich. Die weiten Landschaften der Türkei reichen von schneebedeckten Bergen zu Korallenriffen. Auch die anderen Länder sind alle einzigartig.

programme.desc: Jeremy Wade ist im australischen Outback unterwegs, um den seltenen Süßwassersägerochen zu fangen.

programme.desc: Jeremy Wade ist im südlichen Afrika an den Ufern des Okavango unterwegs.

programme.title: Tödlicher Angriff am Rio Yata
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade geht der Geschichte eines Mannes nach, dem in Bolivien das Gesicht abgerissen wurde.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Handgemacht in Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: In Asien wird Rattan vielseitig verwendet: zur Herstellung von Möbeln, Korbwaren, Wandverkleidungen und Sportbällen. Auch im bergreichen Zentrum von Laos gedeiht die stachelige Rattan-Palme. Wild als Kletter-Liane in den Dschungelwäldern, sowie angebaut auf Feldern. Die Menschen in den Dörfern ringsum leben seit Generationen von Rattan.

programme.title: Peloponnes
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Im Süden Griechenlands am Peloponnes ist der Alltag, hauptsächlich von der Landwirtschaft geprägt. Mit der Rückkehr der jungen Generation auf das Land ihrer Familien keimt Hoffnung: Permakultur und Agroforstwirtschaft sollen das in der Vergangenheit durch Monokulturen und Brände ausgelaugte Land zu neuem Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Freiheit auf Pferderücken
programme.sub-title: Der lange Weg der Nez Perce
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: 1877 weigerten sich rund 750 Angehörige des Stammes der Nez Perce, im Nordwesten der USA, ihre Freiheit aufzugeben und sich in ein Reservat zu begeben. Stattdessen begaben sie sich mit 2.000 Pferden, überwiegend Appaloosas, auf eine abenteuerliche und verlustreiche Flucht über gut 2.000 km quer durch die Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Der Kräutergarten von Java
programme.desc: Die hügelige Landschaft um Bogor ist der Garten Eden Indonesiens: Bekannt für seine artenreiche Vegetation und eine farbenprächtige Gärten. Hier praktizieren die Menschen eine Jahrtausende alte Pflanzenmedizin, genannt JAMU. Einst wurde das Wissen um die Wirkung der Kräuter nur innerhalb von bestimmten Heilerfamilien weitergegeben, doch heute ist es die Alltagsmedizin eines ganzen Volkes.

programme.title: Bangkoks krabbelnde Delikatessen
programme.desc: Bangkoks Vergnügungsviertel Patpong bei Nacht: , Mobile Garküchen und Imbissstände bieten an jeder Straßenecke duftende Köstlichkeiten an. Auch San Supathanakuns Snacks sind sehr beliebt:. Auf ihrem Verkaufskarren liegen in kleinen Schüsseln aufgereiht frittierte Heuschrecken, Wasserkäfer, Ameisensalat, Seidenwürmer und knackige schwarze Skorpione. Es wird gebrutzelt, gebraten und frittiert auf dem kleinen Platz vor den Wohnbaracken direkt neben einer vierspurigen Hauptverkehrsstraße. Etwa 14 Millionen Menschen leben hier, und es werden immer mehr. Viele stammen aus dem bitterarmen Nordosten Thailands - so wie die virtuose 35-jährige Köchin San. Sie kam vor fünf Jahren mit einer besonderen Geschäftsidee: Dem Verkauf von köstlichen Insekten-Snacks in den Straßen Bangkoks. Insekten finden in Thailand immer mehr Liebhaber. Doch Sans Hauptkundschaft sind die jungen Frauen aus ihrer ländlichen Heimat, die oft aus Mangel an Ausbildung ihr Geld in Bangkoks Vergnügungsviertel Patpong mit Prostitution verdienen. Mit ihrem Verdienst kann San die gesamte Großfamilie unterstützen und den Kredit für ein eigenes Haus in ihrem Heimatdorf abzahlen. Dafür musste sie allerdings ihre kleine Tochter zurücklassen - und sie arbeitet täglich fast ohne Pause. Selbst um drei Uhr nachts hat sie noch k ...

programme.title: Mezcal
programme.desc: In Mexico gilt er als hochprozentiges Geschenk der Götter: der Mezcal. Im Rest der Welt ist das Muttergetränk des Tequila vor allem durch die Raupe bekannt, die der Flasche beigefügt ist. Doch Mezcal ist mehr als das - er ist Lebensgefühl und ein wichtiger Wirtschaftsfaktor der verarmten Provinz Oaxaca. Schon die Ureinwohner der mexikanischen Region Oaxaca, die Zapoteken brauten für ihre Riten einen Likör aus wilden Agaven und Heilpflanzen - den Mezcal. Heute wird der traditionelle Mezcal vor allem in Familienbetrieben gebrannt. Die verschiedenen Agavenarten aus der Provinz Oaxaca geben ihm seinen besonderen Geschmack. Mezcalero zu sein gilt hier als angesehener Beruf, viele Familien haben ihre Existenz auf den Anbau und die Verarbeitung der Agaven ausgerichtet. Doch immer mehr große Firmen wollen ihren Anteil an dem populären Getränk, und die kleinen Destillen müssen um ihren Platz auf dem heiß umkämpften Markt ringen.

programme.title: Wycliffe Gordon
programme.sub-title: Wynton Marsalis: In This House, on This Morning
programme.desc: The final concert of the Münchner Klaviersommer 1992 was by Wynton Marsalis and his septet. The 31-years-young star trumpeter performed one of his own jazz suites to the sold-out Philharmonie, under the title of ‘In This House, On This Morning'. The concert covers every jazz style, in composition and improvisation, and in both small and grand forms. Marsalis's Septet was made up of Wess Anderson (alto saxophone), Wycliffe Gordon (trombone), Reginald Veal (bass), Herlin Riley (drums), Todd Williams (tenor saxophone), and Eric Reed (piano).

programme.title: Earl Hines
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Jaco Pastorius
programme.desc: The audience at the Montreal Jazz Festival in Canada was in for a treat on July 3, 1982, as a true musical innovator hit the stage: Jaco Pastorius, who transformed the electric bass into a formidable solo instrument. Combining intricate harmonics, fluid melodies, and unparalleled technical skill, Pastorius left a lasting impact on the music world. In this concert, he is accompanied by Peter Erskine (drums), Don Alias (percussion), Othello Molineaux (steel drums), Bob Mintzer (tenor sax and bass clarinet), and Randy Brecker (trumpet and electronics). They perform “Chicken”, “Donna Lee”, “Mr. Phone Bone”, and “Fannie Mae”. Don't miss this extraordinary opportunity to experience Jaco Pastorius's electrifying performance at the Montreal Jazz Festival 1982!

programme.title: Gil Evans & Ornette Coleman
programme.sub-title: Gil Evans, Ornette Coleman - Schloss Ansbach
programme.desc: This program presents two concerts from Schloss Ansbach in 1978. The first concert features Gil Evans and his orchestra, consisting of Gil Evans on piano, Steve Lacy on soprano saxophone, Arthur Blythe on alto saxophone, Pit Levin on synthesizers, Earl McIntyre on trombone, Lewis Soloff on trumpet, Geoffrey Berlin on bass and Sue Evans on percussion instruments. The second concert features saxophonist Ornette Coleman at the peak of his musically expressive powers. Coleman is joined by Bern Nix on guitar, Charles Ellerbee on guitar, Albert Arnold on bass, and Shannon Jackson on drums and percussion.

programme.title: Raul Midón
programme.desc: Raul Midón appeared at 2017's Sing Jazz Festival in Singapore with double bassist Romeir Mendez and drummer Billy Williams. Blind since birth, Raul Midón is a singer, guitarist, and songwriter from New Mexico. With a vocal range as dynamic as his guitar playing and a remarkable talent for trumpet mimicry, Midón's performances transcend musical boundaries, effortlessly blending rock, jazz, folk, and Latin pop into his unique sound. He has worked with numerous legends, including Bill Withers, Herbie Hancock, Sting, and Dianne Reeves, and his album ‘Bad Ass and Blind' was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best Jazz Vocal Album in 2018. No wonder the Sing Jazz audience were ecstatic!

programme.title: Popa Chubby
programme.sub-title: Popa Chubby - It's A Mighty Hard Road
programme.desc: Popa Chubby, born as Ted Horowitz, is an American blues singer and guitarist, who has become one of the most popular figures of New York's blues scene. Early on in his career he released the album 'Booty and the Beast' (1995), which became one of the 1990s's best-selling blues albums. Chubby describes his own style as "The Stooges meets Buddy Guy, Motörhead meets Muddy Waters, and Jimi Hendrix meets Robert Johnson". As part of the French music festival Blues sur Seine, Chubby and his band played a great blues rock concert, showcasing the artist's powerful and soulful guitar playing. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Simone Signoret on November 8, 2019.

programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Louis Armstrong
programme.desc: Following a highly successful small-group jazz concert at New York Town Hall on May 17, 1947, Armstrong's manager Joe Glaser dissolved the Armstrong big band on August 13, 1947 and established a six-piece small group. This group was called the All Stars, and in 1964 Louis Armstrong recorded his biggest-selling record, Hello, Dolly! He made assorted television appearances, especially in the 1950s and 1960s – the recorded film was a TV Show in Australia when Armstrong was at the peak of his career. Armstrong kept up his busy tour schedule until a few years before his death in 1971. He also toured Africa, Europe, and Asia under sponsorship of the US State Department with great success, earning the nickname ‘Ambassador Satch'.

programme.title: Walter Trout, Johnny Griparic, Teddy Andreadis "Zig Zag" & Michael Leasure
programme.desc: Every year since 1970, the German city of Burghausen has been hosting one of the largest jazz festivals in the world. During Burghausen International Jazz Week, Burghausen becomes a 'Bavarian jazz mecca': guests from all over the world join the Burghausers to enjoy the most wonderful jazz performances as the colorful hustle and bustle of spectators and musicians shake up the city. One of the bands performing here in 2019 is the Walter Trout Band. Trout, who was born in New Jersey and is based in Los Angeles, is a world-famous contemporary blues rock guitarist and vocalist.

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: Dexter Gordon, George Gruntz, Guy Pedersen & Daniel Humair
programme.desc: Dexter Gordon: Live in '63 & '64 features three concerts filmed in Holland, Switzerland, and Belgium that highlight the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. These shows feature legendary side musicians such as Art Taylor (drums) and Kenny Drew (piano), and jazz classics “Blues Walk”, “A Night In Tunisia”, “Body And Soul”, and others. One of the most influential saxophonists in jazz history, Dexter Gordon is captured in sharp form and style in this 70-minute tour de force.

programme.title: Billy Idol
programme.desc: BILLY IDOL an English rock musician, songwriter and actor. Born in Stanmore, Middlesex, Idol first achieved fame in the punk rock era as a member of the band Generation X. Idol then embarked on a successful solo career, and was a member of the MTV-driven "Second British Invasion" of the United States. A series of music videos for songs such as "Dancing with Myself", "White Wedding", "Rebel Yell" and "Eyes Without a Face" made him one of the first MTV stars. Idol continues to tour with guitarist Steve Stevens. Using interviews, news archive and performance this episode reveals the unique aspect of this iconic artist.

programme.title: Costanza Principe
programme.desc: Italian classical pianist Costanza Principe (1993) started playing the piano at age 6, making her public debut at age 7. Before long she would be performing as a soloist with numerous prestigious orchestras in Italy, the UK, France, and South America. Seen here in 2021 at one of Italy's oldest extant Renaissance theatres, the gorgeous Teatro Olimpico in the northern Italian town of Vicenza, Principe performs Johann Sebastian Bach's ‘Concerto italiano' and ‘Ciaccona', as transcribed for piano by Ferruccio Busoni.

programme.title: Les Dissonances & David Grimal
programme.sub-title: Schubert - Symphony No. 8 in B minor, D. 759
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance Les Dissonances perform Franz Schubert's Symphony No. 8 in B minor, D. 759, also known as the ‘Unfinished Symphony'. Schubert started composing the work in 1822, but only completed the first two movements. The first movement, Allegro moderato, has a dark, mysterious mood, which contrasts with the beautiful second movement in E major, Andante con moto. Schubert only penned a couple of measures of the third movement, a Scherzo, in full score. It is not known why the composer never finished his symphony. Although it is not complete, it has become one of Schubert's most popular compositions. This performance was recorded at Cité de la musique in Paris, France, in 2013.

programme.title: Jan Latham-Koenig, Symfonieorkest Vlaanderen & Pascal Amoyel
programme.sub-title: Grieg's Piano Concerto & Beethoven Symphony No. 7
programme.desc: Conductor Jan Latham-Koenig leads the Flanders Symphony Orchestra in this concert recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on April 21, 2016. The program opens with Felix Mendelssohn's concert overture Die Hebriden, Op. 26 (The Hebrides). During a trip to Scotland, the composer was deeply impressed by the natural splendor of Staffa, an island of the Inner Hebrides, which inspired him to compose his concert overture. Next on the program is Edvard Grieg's Piano Concerto in A minor, Op. 16, featuring Pascal Amoyel as the pianist. It is the composer's only concerto. Grieg composed the work in 1868, drawing inspiration from Norwegian folk music. The program ends with Ludwig van Beethoven's Symphony No. 7 in A major, Op. 92. The work is very popular, especially because of its touching second movement. At the Allegretto's 1813 premiere, the audience demanded an immediate encore.

programme.title: Mademoiselle Karen, Jakob Munch, Danish National Symphony Orchestra & Emma Smith
programme.desc: One night only! Welcome to the spectacular and decadent world of The Babylon Hotel, where music pours out of every crevice like bubbling champagne. In this concert, the upper class meets the underworld in a melting pot of euphoria and extravagance, nostalgia and pleasure with a carefree sinfulness only seen in the exuberant nightlife of the 1920s around the world. The concert features iconic music from movies and series, such as The Great Gatsby, Burlesque, and Babylon Berlin. The music is performed by the Danish National Symphony Orchestra and DR Big Band under the direction of Miho Hazama. The concert also features the Moka Efti Orchestra, and singers Madame le Pustra, Emma Smith, Mademoiselle Karen, Jakob Munch, and Nikko Weidemann, as well as dancers of Sweet Burlesque. This performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in May 2023.

programme.title: Thomas Zehetmair, Ivan Fischer & Budapest Festival Orchestra
programme.desc: Iván Fischer conducts the Budapest Festival Orchestra in a concert recorded at the Béla Bartók National Concert Hall in Budapest, Hungary in 2015. The concert opens with Sergei Prokofiev's Overture on Hebrew Themes, Op. 34. After this, Thomas Zehetmair stars as solo violinist in Prokofiev Violin Concerto No. 2, Op. 63. The second part of the concert is features music by Igor Stravinsky. On the program is music composed for the ballet 'Jeu de cartes' (1937) and the Firebird Suite, No. 2 (1919). 'Jeu de cartes' is one of Stravinsky's neo-classical works and consists of three parts ('deals'). The Firebird Suite, No. 2 is based on the music from the ballet of the same name, which was written for Sergei Diaghilev's Ballets Russes and premiered in Paris in 1910.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Erdmännchen
programme.desc: Der Erdmännchen-Nachwuchs in der Kalahari ist der Dürre, Nahrungsknappheit und einer Fülle von Räubern ausgesetzt. Die Hälfte der putzigen Pelztiere überlebt die ersten Monate nicht. Nur die Fürsorge des Clans und eine große Portion Glück kann Erdmännchen-Baby Swift retten. Der viel zu lange ausbleibende Regen drängt die Kolonie immer weiter weg vom sicheren Bau. Schlangen und Greifvögel kreuzen immer wieder die Wege der hungrigen Großfamilie. Auf unbekanntem Territorium und ohne die Möglichkeit in die unterirdischen Gangsysteme zu flüchten, ist die wuselige Truppe Angriffen am Boden und aus der Luft schutzlos ausgeliefert. An den Reviergrenzen kommt es zu Kämpfen mit benachbarten Kolonien, die ihre spärliche Beute verteidigen. Dank des starken Zusammenhalts und Familiensinns meistert Swifts Kolonie jedoch die Durstrecke erfolgreich. Einer von Swifts unerschrockenen Cousins überlebt sogar einen Kobra-Angriff und gibt seiner kleinen Cousine nur wenig später Unterricht im Skorpione-Jagen.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2

Tiefe Schluchten und glasklare Bergseen, artenreiche Trockenwiesen und seltene Moore, majestätische Steinböcke und zurückkehrende Wölfe.
